{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"cadaverous-explorable-goral","description":"## Summary\nAn agent-executed epic cannot be represented in the store as certified/**signed**-closed when\none of its child stories carries an `[operator-attested]` acceptance criterion whose evidence\nlives outside the codebase and outside the executing agent's access — even when every\nengineering acceptance criterion across the whole epic is demonstrably complete and landed on\n`main`. This is a process/tooling gap surfaced while executing epic `bf50-2131-271b-4fdc`\n(graceless-hominine-jerboa); it is NOT a defect in any of that epic's code changes.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Decompose an epic into stories and execute it with an agent (claim → implement → land each\n   child through the Gerrit gate).\n2. Include among the children a story whose acceptance criteria contain an `[operator-attested]`\n   item whose admissible evidence is inherently out-of-band — e.g. 5f39-cb52-9355-492f AC3:\n   configured GitHub repo VARIABLES (`JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_PROJECT`,\n   `ACLI_VERSION`/`ACLI_SHA256`), a configured SECRET (`JIRA_API_TOKEN`), a provisioned\n   dedicated Jira test project, and the URL of a green `workflow_dispatch` run in which the live\n   Jira test EXECUTED (not all-skip).\n3. Have the agent complete and LAND every code change (all children `Verified +1` AND\n   `LLM-Review +1`, merged to `main`).\n4. Attempt to close that child, then the epic.\n\n## Expected\nWith all engineering acceptance criteria met and landed, the epic — and every child — can be\nclosed with a completion-verifier **signature** (certified), such that the store durably\nrecords the epic as fully certified when the work is in fact complete.\n\n## Actual\n- The child's completion verifier passes every CODE criterion but FAILS the single\n  `[operator-attested]` criterion, because the agent has neither the access nor the\n  authorization to produce the required out-of-band evidence (repo secrets/variables, a live\n  Jira project, an observed green canary run), and no concrete attestation (run URL/id/timestamp)\n  therefore exists to record.\n- The child can only be **force-closed UNSIGNED**.\n- The epic's own acceptance criterion requires \"all child stories closed (**signed**)\", so the\n  epic's completion verifier fails on that criterion and the epic can only be **force-closed\n  UNSIGNED** as well.\n- Net: an epic whose entire engineering scope is complete and landed cannot be represented as\n  certified/signed, purely because one child's evidence is out-of-band from the agent's reach.\n\n## Evidence / Impact\n- Concretely observed on epic `bf50-2131-271b-4fdc`: 19/19 stories implemented and merged to\n  `main` (Gerrit changes 537–555 + 559); 18/19 children closed SIGNED (plan-review +\n  completion-verifier); child `5f39-cb52-9355-492f` and the epic closed UNSIGNED via force-close.\n- Full trail (per-story claims, RED/teeth evidence, landing, the force-close reasoning, and a\n  dedicated PROBLEM RECORD entry) is in session log `25f1-5000-760d-4c2b`\n  (plump-kitschy-meadowlark), linked to this bug.\n- Impact: the \"signed = fully certified\" invariant cannot be earned for any epic that contains\n  an operator-attested criterion the agent cannot attest; such epics are indistinguishable in\n  the store (both unsigned) from epics whose OWN engineering work genuinely failed verification.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The problem is reproducible and characterized: an agent-executed epic with all\n      engineering ACs complete + landed, plus one child bearing an out-of-band\n      `[operator-attested]` criterion the agent cannot attest, results in unsigned closure of\n      both the child and the epic.\n- [ ] The gap is documented with the concrete instance (epic bf50, child 5f39) and its evidence\n      (the specific out-of-band items required, and why the agent could not produce them).\n- [ ] This bug links to the full session log capturing the run and the problem record.","id":"02a3-9004-ed30-4395","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Agent-executed epic cannot close SIGNED when a child has an operator-attested criterion the agent cannot attest"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783829097061953001,"uuid":"d3e8844a-cf78-44b4-9dba-6f097439b4fe"}